# Next.js (marketing)

## Defaults

- Prefer **Server Components**; add `"use client"` only for interactivity, hooks, or browser APIs.
- Use static generation where possible (`generateStaticParams` for blog slugs).
- Keep `layout.tsx` for fonts, global styles, and shell providers only.

## Routes

- One primary concern per `page.tsx`: metadata + composition.
- Colocate route-specific sections in `src/components/marketing/`, not bloated page files.

## Data

- Read marketing copy from `src/content/` or `src/lib/` helpers — not fetches to CMS unless explicitly added.

## Images

- Use `next/image` with configured remote patterns (`next.config.ts`).
- Provide meaningful `alt` text for marketing imagery.

## Future

- API routes under `src/app/api/**` follow `marketing-api-future.mdc` when introduced.
